<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF9FFFE339D30F1444E2BE57" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF9FFFE339D30F1446B3BE7A" blockId="17.[136,1452,1057,2070]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE339D30F1447E6BF13" bold="true" box="[136,200,1058,1084]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Trees</emphasis>
5–20(–32) m tall, rhytidome suberous; 1 pair of nectaries present on the branch right below the insertion of the petiole (a nectary at each side), slightly verruciform to depressed. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE33A260F7344E1BF70" bold="true" box="[893,975,1093,1119]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Leaves</emphasis>
with 4 pairs of pinnae, opposite; (4–)5–6 pairs of leaflets, opposite to subopposite; petiolar nectaries absent; leaflets 1.8–5.3 × 
<quantity id="640843B7FF9FFFE33D110F5E4398BFAD" box="[1098,1206,1128,1154]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" unit="cm" value="3.15" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.3">2.3–4 cm</quantity>
, apex usually slightly emarginate, sometimes round, rarely truncate or asymmetrically round, very rarely acute, margin flat, coriaceous, discolor, upper surface glabrous, velutinous only along the midrib, lower surface velutinous, unilateral tuft of trichomes on lower surface absent. Inflorescences of simple thyrsi; cymulae of geminate to ternate spikes, spikes 
<quantity id="640843B7FF9FFFE33C4D0FE44244BFC3" box="[1302,1386,1234,1260]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" unit="cm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8 cm</quantity>
long; spike prophylls deciduous, not observed. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE33B290FC345FFBE20" bold="true" box="[626,721,1269,1295]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Flowers</emphasis>
monoclinous, whitish to greenish white, anther gland sessile. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE339D30E2E47E8BE1D" bold="true" box="[136,198,1304,1330]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Fruit</emphasis>
a nucoid legume, cochleate, subturgid, 8–10 × 3– 
<quantity id="640843B7FF9FFFE33BA40E2E4417BE1D" box="[767,825,1304,1330]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
, valves woody, light-brown yellowish and ferruginouspulverulent, glabrescent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF9FFFE339E60E6844E2BE57" blockId="17.[136,1452,1057,2070]" box="[189,972,1374,1401]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE339E60E68468EBE57" bold="true" box="[189,416,1374,1400]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Vernacular names:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE338E70E6845E6BE57" box="[444,712,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Rosquinha, Barbatimão</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FF9FFFE33B8D0E684431BE57" box="[726,799,1374,1400]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF9FFFE33A710E6944EEBE57" box="[810,960,1374,1401]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF9FFFE339E60EB7422CBDF7" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF9FFFE339E60EB74562BD06" blockId="17.[136,1452,1057,2070]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE339E60EB746D2BEB4" bold="true" box="[189,508,1409,1436]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF9FFFE33B430EB74471BEB4" authorityName="E. M. O. Martins" authorityYear="1980" box="[536,863,1409,1435]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fissuratum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE33B430EB74471BEB4" box="[536,863,1409,1435]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Stryphnodendron fissuratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as having a restricted distribution in northern 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF9FFFE338CA0E934575BE90" box="[401,603,1445,1471]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Mato Grosso state</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FF9FFFE33B250E9345ECBE90" box="[638,706,1445,1471]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF9FFFE33B8B0E934459BE90" author="Martins, E. M. O." box="[720,887,1445,1471]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" pagination="83 - 84" refId="ref43229" refString="Martins, E. M. O. (1980 a) A Stryphnodendron new to the Amazonian flora. Contributions from the University of Michigan Herbarium 14: 83 - 84." type="journal article" year="1980">Martins 1980a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF9FFFE33ADA0E9344E9BE90" author="Martins, E. M. O." box="[897,967,1445,1471]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" pagination="729 - 732" refId="ref43262" refString="Martins, E. M. O. (1980 b) Distribuicao geografica do genero Stryphnodendron com descricao de nova especie (Leg., Mim.). Revista Brasileira de Biologia 40 (4): 729 - 732." type="journal article" year="1980">1980b</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF9FFFE33AA60E934316BE90" author="Martins, E. M. O." box="[1021,1080,1445,1471]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" pagination="3 - 100" refId="ref43305" refString="Martins, E. M. O. (1981) Stryphnodendron Mart. (Leguminosae-Mimosoideae) com especial referencia aos taxa amazonicos. Leandra 10 - 11: 3 - 100." type="journal article" year="1981">1981</bibRefCitation>
), being usually found in cerradão and semideciduous forests. This study expanded the species´s known distribution to the Lago do Cedro Extractive Reserve in 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF9FFFE3385E0EDD46ADBD29" box="[261,387,1515,1542]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
, and the 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF9FFFE338BD0EDD459EBD2A" box="[486,688,1515,1541]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Santa Cruz region</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FF9FFFE33B890EDD4409BD2A" box="[722,807,1515,1541]" name="Bolivia" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, in a mosaic vegetation including semi-deciduous forests, wooded savannas and flooded savannas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF9FFFE339E60D07422CBDF7" blockId="17.[136,1452,1057,2070]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">
The herbarium sampling of this species is rather scarce, and the labels frequently refer to it as being rare in the collecting sites. In addition to ecological issues that may be associated with the low frequency of the species, the anthropic factor seems to be contributing to its scarcity. The species is considered toxic to the cattle, as described at herbarium labels and from talks with locals during expeditions to Central 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FF9FFFE33AE80DAD44D4BD9A" box="[947,1018,1691,1717]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and further supported by toxicological studies (
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF9FFFE339BF0D8846F5BDF6" author="Rodrigues, A. S. &amp; Chaves, N. S. T. &amp; Damasceno, A. D. &amp; Trindade, B. R. &amp; Martins, G. H. L. &amp; Arantes, A. F." box="[228,475,1726,1753]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" pagination="119 - 126" refId="ref44440" refString="Rodrigues, A. S., Chaves, N. S. T., Damasceno, A. D., Trindade, B. R., Martins, G. H. L. &amp; Arantes, A. F. (2005) Aspectos clinicos da intoxicacao experimental de bovinos pelos frutos de Stryphnodendron fissuratum Mart. (&quot; rosquinha &quot;). Ciencia Animal Brasileira 6: 119 - 126." type="journal article" year="2005">
Rodrigues 
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE3383B0D8946B7BDF7" box="[352,409,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
), which leads farmers to cut individuals of this species indiscriminately.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF9FFFE339E60DD74323BC4A" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF9FFFE339E60DD74323BC4A" blockId="17.[136,1452,1057,2070]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE339E60DD74673BDD4" bold="true" box="[189,349,1761,1787]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Conservation</emphasis>
:—Near Threatened (NT) [AOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FF9FFFE33B800DD4447BBDD4" box="[731,853,1761,1788]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" unit="km" value="32.0">32.000 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFF9FFFE33A0E0DD74473BDC0" attach="left" box="[853,861,1761,1775]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">2</superScript>
, EOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FF9FFFE33AEE0DD74340BDD4" box="[949,1134,1761,1787]" metricMagnitude="8" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.49939603" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" unit="km" value="149939.603">149,939.603 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFF9FFFE33D350DD74358BDC0" attach="left" box="[1134,1142,1761,1775]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">2</superScript>
] The area of occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF9FFFE339D30C3346E8BC30" authorityName="E. M. O. Martins" authorityYear="1980" box="[136,454,1797,1823]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fissuratum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF9FFFE339D30C3346E8BC30" box="[136,454,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">Stryphnodendron fissuratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger than that defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF9FFFE33A4A0C33448EBC30" author="IUCN" box="[785,928,1797,1823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" refId="ref42510" refString="IUCN (2012) IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria version 3.1. 2 nd ed. Available from: http: // jr. iucnredlist. org / documents / redlist _ cats _ crit _ en. pdf (accessed 15 May 2018)" type="book" year="2012">IUCN (2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF9FFFE33AF10C3344CABC30" author="IUCN" box="[938,996,1797,1823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" refId="ref42556" refString="IUCN (2022) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria Version 15 (January 2022). Available from: https: // nc. iucnredlist. org / redlist / content / attachment _ files / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 11 March 2022)" type="journal volume" year="2022">2022</bibRefCitation>
) criteria to be considered an Endangered species. However, since it is commonly suppressed in areas used for pasture and is frequently referred as rare in its occurrence sites, the species is more adequately considered as.Near Threatened.
</paragraph>
